  "time_ut": 1657885120,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0da7-\u0db6\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0da7 28\u0dad\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d9c\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0dc4\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Mahinda-Basil banned from traveling abroad until 28",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Supreme Court issued an interim order today (15) prohibiting former Prime Minister Mahinda Rajapaksa and former Finance Minister Basil Rajapaksa from traveling abroad until the 28th of this month without the permission of the Supreme Court.",
        "This interim order was issued when the petitions filed by social activist Chandra Jayaratne and other petitioners were called before a five-judge bench of the Supreme Court today (15).",
        "This motion was filed by Chief Justice Jayantha Jayasuriya, Bhuvaneka Aluvihare, Priyantha Jayawardena, Vijith Malalgoda and L. D. B. Dehideniya was considered before a panel of five judges.",
        "Former Central Bank Governor Professor W. D. Lakshman and former Secretary of the Ministry of Finance S. R. Mr. Atigala also promised before the court that they will not go abroad until the 27th of this month.",
        "Another respondent here, former Central Bank Governor Mr. Ajith Nivard Kabral also promised in the court that he will not go abroad without the permission of the Supreme Court.",
        "This motion has been filed by social activist Chandra Jayaratne and famous Sri Lankan swimmer Julian Bowling.",
        "The petitioners have filed these petitions before the Supreme Court asking for an investigation and action against those responsible for the country's economic crisis."
      ],
